agency_open_data_plan:
The Department of Administrative Services (DAS) is the central administrative agency of Oregon state government. Our mission is to lead state agencies through collaboration in service of Oregonians. DAS works to effectively implement the policy and financial decisions made by the Governor and the Oregon Legislature. The department also sets and monitors high standards of accountability to ensure that state government uses tax dollars productively. To fulfill its mission, DAS supports state agencies by providing a strong and stable management infrastructure. As part of this effort, DAS works with private enterprise, citizens, and other government entities to develop an efficient service delivery system.

DAS documented 28 datasets in its initial data inventory. While many datasets are statewide in scope, they represent only datasets that DAS (as a distinct agency) manages in its portfolio. The sensitive nature of DAS data, unique characteristics of each system, and differing technical readiness all necessitate intentional data preparation before publishing additional DAS datasets. DAS manages many systems of record for statewide operations that often contain sensitive data not partitioned for publication, and DAS datasets have been developed using a wide array of technical approaches across multiple decades. DAS open data efforts over the next two years will therefore focus on planning for additional publication where possible, including: 
1) ensuring a full and complete data inventory; 
2) resolving technical roadblocks in readying relevant legacy systems for publication; 
3) sufficiently partitioning data across relevant datasets; and 
4) advocating for and aligning any approved DAS investments in technical infrastructure that can equip open data readiness.
